[SN]TITLE[SN]
Flat open to London stock market

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
(Open): London's benchmark index of blue-chip stocks dipped extremely slightly in early trade on Wednesday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Not long after open the FTSE 100 was down by just a quarter of a point,  at 6753.54.
Among the winners was supermarket chain Sainsbury's, ahead by 2.33%, despite reporting a sixth straight quarter of falling sales.
Other early gainers included fellow grocer Tesco, ahead by 1.46%,  and also bank Standard Chartered, up by 3.14%.
Miners Anglo American and Rio Tinto were ahead by 1.79% and 1.31% respectively.
Biggest faller was Weir Group, down by 2.13%, after saying it expected its full-year results to be more weighted towards the second half of the financial year.
Imperial Tobacco Group was down by 1%, after calls for a tobacco levy to help smokers quit.
